00:27:41.270 --> 00:27:43.250 align:middle line:84%
Was there a population
boom after this?

00:27:43.250 --> 00:27:44.960 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: That's a
great question, Jay.

00:27:44.960 --> 00:27:48.000 align:middle line:84%
And this was no
exception to that.

00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:51.320 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, it was encouraged
because the population had been

00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:56.300 align:middle line:84%
so decimated that
there were within each

00:27:56.300 --> 00:28:00.950 align:middle line:84%
of the small communities--
because they didn't have

00:28:00.950 --> 00:28:04.730 align:middle line:84%
mainstream media
or media outlets,

00:28:04.730 --> 00:28:08.600 align:middle line:84%
the way that they were able
to disseminate information

00:28:08.600 --> 00:28:12.530 align:middle line:84%
were like neighborhood
groups in which

00:28:12.530 --> 00:28:14.450 align:middle line:84%
there were families
that were neighbors,

00:28:14.450 --> 00:28:17.660 align:middle line:84%
and that neighborhood
group had information

00:28:17.660 --> 00:28:19.860 align:middle line:84%
and they disseminated
amongst their neighbors.

00:28:19.860 --> 00:28:21.110 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: This was after the war?

00:28:21.110 --> 00:28:22.190 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: After the war.

00:28:22.190 --> 00:28:24.750 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So you didn't even
have media after the war?

00:28:24.750 --> 00:28:25.550 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: Nope.

00:28:25.550 --> 00:28:28.820 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: Well how are you
getting mass orders and people

00:28:28.820 --> 00:28:30.092 align:middle line:90%
telling people what to do?

00:28:30.092 --> 00:28:32.300 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: That's where the
neighborhood groups come in.

00:28:32.300 --> 00:28:33.592 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: That would take forever.

00:28:33.592 --> 00:28:35.660 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Well you've
got to figure,

00:28:35.660 --> 00:28:41.370 align:middle line:84%
they also had the benefits
of communication technology.

00:28:41.370 --> 00:28:45.820 align:middle line:84%
So they were able to
communicate in real time,

00:28:45.820 --> 00:28:50.000 align:middle line:84%
and so they were able
to transfer information

00:28:50.000 --> 00:28:54.280 align:middle line:84%
in the form of, OK,
here's the production

00:28:54.280 --> 00:28:57.898 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to have, and
it was written out and something

00:28:57.898 --> 00:28:59.440 align:middle line:84%
that they were able
to take with them

00:28:59.440 --> 00:29:01.285 align:middle line:84%
and share with their
neighborhood groups.

00:29:01.285 --> 00:29:02.660 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: You would
need blueprints.

00:29:02.660 --> 00:29:04.210 align:middle line:90%
You would need all sorts of--

00:29:04.210 --> 00:29:05.650 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: All digitized.

00:29:05.650 --> 00:29:10.160 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So they had digital--
did they have pads, anything?

00:29:10.160 --> 00:29:12.910 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: They had small
handheld computer systems

00:29:12.910 --> 00:29:15.890 align:middle line:84%
that they were able to share,
and every single family

00:29:15.890 --> 00:29:16.690 align:middle line:90%
had one.

00:29:16.690 --> 00:29:18.148 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: Well that's
kind of a media.

00:29:18.148 --> 00:29:19.280 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: Yep, true.

00:29:19.280 --> 00:29:20.080 align:middle line:90%
True.

00:29:20.080 --> 00:29:22.690 align:middle line:84%
But I guess I was thinking
along the lines of--

00:29:22.690 --> 00:29:23.490 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Television.

00:29:23.490 --> 00:29:26.280 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: --Television or
newspaper or a magazine print

00:29:26.280 --> 00:29:27.080 align:middle line:90%
media.

00:29:27.080 --> 00:29:28.752 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Did they have internet?

00:29:28.752 --> 00:29:30.460 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: They did have
a form of internet,

00:29:30.460 --> 00:29:33.310 align:middle line:84%
and it was specifically
and very strictly

00:29:33.310 --> 00:29:37.150 align:middle line:84%
regulated just for the
rebuilding purposes.

00:29:37.150 --> 00:29:39.550 align:middle line:84%
So if you needed information
on a particular element

00:29:39.550 --> 00:29:41.980 align:middle line:84%
because you were going to be
mixing two metals together

00:29:41.980 --> 00:29:44.560 align:middle line:84%
and you needed to know
the right combinations,

00:29:44.560 --> 00:29:45.820 align:middle line:90%
that information was there.

00:29:45.820 --> 00:29:49.030 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: And how much help did
you, IDARF, give these people

00:29:49.030 --> 00:29:50.870 align:middle line:90%
at the end of the war?

00:29:50.870 --> 00:29:54.850 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: I wasn't there for
the initial stages when

00:29:54.850 --> 00:29:56.490 align:middle line:90%
they had set all this up.

00:29:56.490 --> 00:30:01.060 align:middle line:84%
I found out about how they
set it up after the fact

00:30:01.060 --> 00:30:05.200 align:middle line:84%
and had seen some
of the legacy issues

00:30:05.200 --> 00:30:07.930 align:middle line:90%
that were still being used.

00:30:07.930 --> 00:30:11.470 align:middle line:84%
So I found out about
that after the fact.

00:30:11.470 --> 00:30:12.640 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't there.

